gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Magic 104, Cavaliers 94
gameRecap.excerpt: The Magic outscored the Cavaliers 53-40 in the second half as they defeated the Cavaliers 104-94. Paolo Banchero led the Magic with 20 points, 10 rebounds, and four assists as Franz Wagner added 19 points, eight rebounds, and four assists. Darius Garland led the Cavaliers with a season-high 36 points, six rebounds, and five assists as Donovan Mitchell added 22 points. The Magic snapped the Cavs three-game win streak and improve to 16-7 on the year as the Cavaliers move to 13-10.
